
# Git commit message template
#
# Conventions (common in open-source projects):
#   type(scope): summary
#
# Guidelines:
# - Keep the summary <= 50 characters.
# - Wrap body lines at <= 72 characters.
# - Use the body to explain WHAT and WHY (not every HOW).
#
# Suggested types (type : Chinese meaning):
# - feat    : 新功能
# - fix     : 修复 bug
# - docs    : 文档变更
# - style   : 代码风格（不影响逻辑）
# - refactor: 重构（不改变功能）
# - perf    : 性能优化
# - test    : 测试相关
# - chore   : 构建/维护相关
# - ci      : CI 配置相关
# - build   : 构建系统相关
# - revert  : 回退先前提交
#
# Footer:
# - Breaking changes:
#     BREAKING CHANGE: <what changed and what users must do>
# - Issue/PR references:
#     Issue: #123
#     PR: #456
# - Sign-off (only if your project requires it):
#     Signed-off-by: Your Name <you@example.com>
#
# Example (regular commit):
# feat(cli): add interactive commit message generator
#
# Changes: Implement an interactive CLI flow to help users generate commit
# messages following the repository template. Add basic validation for type
# and optional scope.
#
# Testing: Add unit tests and a CLI integration test verifying generated
# messages match the template rules.
#
# Example (breaking change):
# feat(config): migrate configuration format to v2
#
# Changes: Update config parsing to support v2 schema and add migration
# notes to documentation.
#
# Testing: Add fixtures for v1/v2 and regression tests for config loading.
#
# BREAKING CHANGE: Configuration file format changed from v1 to v2; manual
# migration of configuration items is required.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Write your commit message below (comment lines starting with # are ignored)

docs(changelog): 规范 Unreleased 分类并补充比较链接

Changes:
- 将 Unreleased 重组为 Keep a Changelog 的分类（Added / Changed），并将现有未发布条目按类型归类。
- 在 Unreleased 段落顶部添加版本更新建议（MINOR）。
- 在文件末尾添加比较链接 `[Unreleased]` 与最近发布 tag 的链接，便于生成发布对比。

Testing:
- 手动校验 CHANGELOG.md 内容格式与链接。
- 建议在 CI 中运行 markdownlint 与校验脚本来验证格式一致性。

